<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,150,176]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Сomparison</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2017" box="[483,609,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Caledomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,609,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Caledomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a considerable similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[1031,1141,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1141,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Adocimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2016" box="[1155,1295,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Allenipeplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1155,1295,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Allenipeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2017" box="[1309,1437,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brittonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1309,1437,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Brittonoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[199,320,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,320,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male anal sclerite of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2017" box="[622,931,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Caledomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extraordinarius">
<emphasis box="[622,931,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Caledomus extraordinarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to that in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirejtshuk" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1281,1374,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1374,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Cillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Afro-Malgasy (Afro-Madagascan) areas and members of both demonstrate a significant similarity in their general appearance. However 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk et Kovalev" authorityYear="2017" box="[496,622,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Caledomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[496,622,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Caledomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirejtshuk" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[777,870,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[777,870,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Cillaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the characters of the head (pregenal processes wider and more projecting anteriorly, shape of mentum and hypostomal sinuses), and also in the widely rounded anterior angles and clearly explanate sides of pronotum, subpentagonal scutellar shield, abdominal laterosternites V and VI clearly widened posteriorly, presence of a chin piece of the anterior edge of prosternum, elevated median part of prosternum, concavity at the middle of the hypopygidium of both sexes, and in the structure of the anal male sclerite and genitalia of both sexes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,474,501]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Notes on bionomy</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[489,537,475,501]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
series was collected in the base the Bromeliad leaves (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="226 - 242" refId="ref106508" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2016) A new genus of the subfamily Cillaeinae (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from the Philippines and New Guinea with notes on the taxonomy and phylogeny of the subfamily. Zootaxa, 4205 (3), 226 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.3.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,550,546,573]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Composition and distribution</emphasis>
. This genus includes only the 
<typeStatus box="[883,931,547,573]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V." box="[1031,1350,547,573]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="443 - 450" refId="ref106576" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. &amp; Kovalev, A. V. (2017) Caledomus gen. nov., a new cillaeine genus (Coleoptera, Nitidulidae) from New Caledonia and taxonomic notes. Zootaxa, 4277 (3), 443 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4277.3.9" type="journal article" year="2017">Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
), which is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[322,498,583,609]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
